{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.27",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 27,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 27",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 27 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:1",
      "text": "And Job again took up his discourse, and said:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:2",
      "text": "“As God lives, who has taken away my right, and the Almighty, who has made my soul bitter;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:3",
      "text": "as long as my breath is in me, and the spirit of God is in my nostrils;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:4",
      "text": "my lips will not speak falsehood, and my tongue will not utter deceit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:5",
      "text": "Far be it from me to say that you are right; till I die I will not put away my integrity from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:6",
      "text": "I hold fast my righteousness, and will not let it go; my heart does not reproach me for any of my days.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:7",
      "text": "“Let my enemy be as the wicked, and let him that rises up against me be as the unrighteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:8",
      "text": "For what is the hope of the godless when God cuts him off, when God takes away his life?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:9",
      "text": "Will God hear his cry, when trouble comes upon him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:10",
      "text": "Will he take delight in the Almighty? Will he call upon God at all times?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:11",
      "text": "I will teach you concerning the hand of God; what is with the Almighty I will not conceal.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:12",
      "text": "Behold, all of you have seen it yourselves; why then have you become altogether vain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:13",
      "text": "“This is the portion of a wicked man with God, and the heritage which oppressors receive from the Almighty:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:14",
      "text": "If his children are multiplied, it is for the sword; and his offspring have not enough to eat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:15",
      "text": "Those who survive him the pestilence buries, and their widows make no lamentation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:16",
      "text": "Though he heap up silver like dust, and pile up clothing like clay;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:17",
      "text": "he may pile it up, but the just will wear it, and the innocent will divide the silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:18",
      "text": "The house which he builds is like a spider's web, like a booth which a watchman makes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:19",
      "text": "He goes to bed rich, but will do so no more; he opens his eyes, and his wealth is gone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:20",
      "text": "Terrors overtake him like a flood; in the night a whirlwind carries him off.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:21",
      "text": "The east wind lifts him up and he is gone; it sweeps him out of his place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:22",
      "text": "It hurls at him without pity; he flees from its power in headlong flight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.27.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 27,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 27:23",
      "text": "It claps its hands at him, and hisses at him from its place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
